The paper discusses a new IDE for ACL2, a theorem proving system and programming language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses user feedback and the design of the interface, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions property-based testing and automated interpretation of properties, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and emerging technologies (cs.ET). Finally, the paper discusses the user interface and user experience, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
